titleInfo.title: USA v. Digiorgio et al
titleInfo.subTitle: MEMORANDUM AND ORDER regarding Motions to Suppress 18 and 20 as to defendants Christopher G. Digiorgio and Dominick C. Digiorgio. 1. The government is given until May 30, 2008 to file a brief addressing the factual and legal issues raised in defendant Christopher DiGiorgios brief and during the parties' oral argument at the conclusion of the evidentiary hearing. Any issues not briefed by the government as required under this order will be deemed conceded by the government. 2. Defendant Christopher DiGiorgio is given five days thereafter to submit a responsive brief, at which time, his motion will be deemed submitted. Ordered by Magistrate Judge David L. Piester. titleInfo.title: USA v. Digiorgio et al
titleInfo.subTitle: REPORT AND RECOMMENDATION the Honorable Richard G. Kopf,United States District Judge, that: a. Defendant Dominick DiGiorgios motion to suppress, filing 18, be denied. b. Defendant Christopher DiGiorgio's motion to suppress, filing 20, be denied to extent that it seeks suppression of evidence based on the allegedly illegal traffic stop, and that the motion be granted in all other respects. The parties are notified that a failure to object to this recommendation in accordance with the local rules of practice may be held to be a waiver of any right to appeal the district judge's adoption of this recommendation.
